creator: noah.drach@gmail.com
text:
I am running distributed testing.
The master is located on a win2008R2 machine and the slaves are located on 2 Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 5.5 (Tikanga) machines.

i see in the jmeter-server.log the following errors at the begining and the end of the test.

ERROR - jmeter.util.BeanShellInterpreter: Error invoking bsh method: eval   In file: inline evaluation of: ``testStarted(1.2.3.4);'' Encountered "( 1.2.3" at line 1, column 12. 

ERROR - jmeter.util.BeanShellInterpreter: Error invoking bsh method: eval   In file: inline evaluation of: ``testEnded(1.2.3.4);'' Encountered "( 1.2 .3" at line 1, column 10. 

started discussing this issue in the mailing list - where it was note that it looks like a defect.

http://jmeter.512774.n5.nabble.com/Error-at-the-end-of-a-distributed-test-tt5717287.html
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 55163 ***
